clash_group_id.notes: Unique ID of the assigned clash group

issue_id.notes: Issue Id associated with the clash clash group

description.notes: Description of the purpose of the issue

status.notes: Unique identifier of the current status of the issue

clash_test_id.notes: Unique id of the clash test

model_set_id.notes: A coordination space ID uniquely identifies combinations of models in a clash group, like 'scope 1' for models A & B, and 'scope 2' for models A & C.

created_at_model_set_version.notes: A coordination space version number uniquely identifies varying model combinations in a clash group. For instance, 'scope version 1' could represent models A v1 & B v1, while 'scope version 2' may denote models A v1 & B v2.

created_at.notes: Date and time the clash group was marked as an issue

created_by.notes: Autodesk ID of the user who marked the clash group as an issue.

clash_group_id.notes: Id of the issue clash group

clash_id.notes: Id of the clash associated with the clash group, corresponding with the clash ID field in the clash result resources available via the API (see API documentation for more details).

model_set_id.notes: A coordination space ID uniquely identifies combinations of models in a clash test, like 'scope 1' for models A & B, and 'scope 2' for models A & C.

model_set_version.notes: A coordination space version ID uniquely identifies varying model combinations in a clash test. For instance, 'scope version 1' could represent models A v1 & B v1, while 'scope version 2' may denote models A v1 & B v2.

root_folder_urn.notes: Unique Resource Name of the clash test root folder

started_at.notes: Date and time the clash job started (UTC)

completed_at.notes: Date and time the clash job finished (UTC)

status.notes: The status of the clash test; Pending, Processing, Successful, Failed

backend_type.notes: The type of the coordination space; Projects created before November 2022 will be 0 = V1, after will be 1 = V2.  Refer to Coordination Space Versions in Model Coordination help files for further information.

clash_group_id.notes: Unique ID of the clash group classified as not-an-issue

reason.notes: Reason why the clash group was marked as not-an-issue

title.notes: Title of the closed clash group classified as not-an-issue

description.notes: Description of the closed clash group

clash_test_id.notes: Unique id of the clash test

model_set_id.notes: A coordination space ID uniquely identifies combinations of models in a clash group classified as not-an-issue, like 'scope 1' for models A & B, and 'scope 2' for models A & C.

created_at_model_set_version.notes: A coordination space version number uniquely identifies varying model combinations in a classified as not-an-issue. For instance, 'scope version 1' could represent models A v1 & B v1, while 'scope version 2' may denote models A v1 & B v2.

created_at.notes: Date and time the clash group was marked as not-an-issue

created_by.notes: Autodesk ID of the user who marked the clash group as not-an-issue.
